.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]CanvasGradient\f[B]\f[R] interface represents an \c
.UR https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Opaque_data_type
opaque object
.UE \c
\ describing a gradient.
It is returned by the methods
\f[CR]CanvasRenderingContext2D.createLinearGradient()\f[R],
\f[CR]CanvasRenderingContext2D.createConicGradient()\f[R] or
\f[CR]CanvasRenderingContext2D.createRadialGradient()\f[R].
.PP
It can be used as a \f[CR]fillStyle\f[R] or \f[CR]strokeStyle\f[R].
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
\f[I]As an opaque object, there is no exposed property.\f[R]
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
